Name: RACS
notes: base catalogue. nsources is components but there are 2123638 islands. Peak flux and int flux of components (also int flux of island should I use that?)

Name: HACT
notes: targeted. based on AT20G. Visual inspection suggests 50 arcsec radius would be acceptable. Integrated flux

Name: HACT90
notes: targeted based on AT20G and radius based on above

Name: GLEAM
notes: integrated flux

Name: VLASS
notes: integrated flux for all sky north of dec=-40 with area calculated. First look so 15% flux underestimate

Name: VLSSr
notes: peak flux with area calculated approximate from section 6 of paper. Corrects flux errors in vlss

Name: AT20G
notes: peak flux only but these are all compact, so fine to assume peak approx. = integrated

Name: NVSS
notes: integrated flux only

Name: FIRST
notes: no errors. From reading paper (esp. p10) it looks like 10% or 1mJy whichever is greater is reasonable)

Name: SUMSS
notes: is MOST the same as the molongolo radio telescope? Flux limit is 10 at dec > -50

Name: TXS
notes: integrated flux only. from 1974-83 so could be too old? The area is calculated from the dec limits of dec = -35.5 to dec = 71.5. Paper says synthesised beam = 12.7arcmin^2

Name: PMNZ
notes: options are Flux or Gflux where Gflux is the flux density derived from a gaussian not of fixed width. So these should be the same for point sources but for extended we want Gflux

Name: SPASS
notes: peak and integrated

Name: C1813
notes: collects other survey data too. Only ~42 sources observed. Visual inspection of matches

Name: C1813_new
notes: collects other survey data too. New data is indicated by an asterisk in the "n_" columns and the 2700 column if new is actually at 2300MHz

Name: PKSCAT90
notes: no uncertainties. BEWARE because we don't know where these fluxes are coming from. Use 15%

Name: Ricci06
notes: has errors with 250 sources from a previous >1Jy sample at 5GHz. 99% match radius added manually

Name: WISH
notes: has peak and integrated flux with some errors. Is a WENSS extension in the sourthern sky. Beam size from specfind. BEWARE take it out because it's unreliable. Use 15% errors

Name: MRC
notes: integrated flux. Not sure what to do about 99% match as my code says it should be zero.

Name: ATPMN
notes: 5 and 8 for a sample of PMN sources but should be covered by AT20G! Uses archival data from ATOA

Name: CCA
notes: Targeted based on Parkes 4C and Ohio. Integrated fluxes and I guess use 15% errors. Other flux lim is 2Jy at 80MHz
